entries.name: KintoAppRegistry
entries.description: Central system contract defining addresses that are allowed to be called by EOAs. The modified Kinto node reads this configuration and drops all other transactions from EOAs (enforced by a modified state transition function). Accordingly, users can only transact from their smart wallets.

event RoleRevoked(bytes32 indexed role, address indexed account, address indexed sender)
event RootUpdated(bytes32 indexed newRoot, bytes32 indexed oldRoot)
event UserClaimed(address indexed user, uint256 indexed amount)
event UserEngenClaimed(address indexed user, uint256 indexed amount)
function claim(bytes32[] proof, address user, uint256 totalUserTokens)
function getRewards(uint256 fromTime, uint256 toTime) view returns (uint256)
function hasRole(bytes32 role, address account) view returns (bool)
function upgradeToAndCall(address newImplementation, bytes data) payable
